$ gflags.exe

*Microsoft® NT Global Flags Manipulator*


{ Registry settings

  Which features are enabled for all processes running on a is stored in the → Windows/registry in the value `GlobalFlags` under the key
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/System/CurrentControlSet/Control/Session-Manager[`HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager`]

  In order for changes to take effect, the computer needs to be restarted.

  gh|Windows-Pics|/Program-Files-x86/Windows-Kits/n/Debuggers/_arch_/gflags.exe/registry.png||


}
{ Kernel flag settings

  Changing Kernel flag settings have immediate effect. These settings are not permanently stored, so their modification is lost if a computer is restarted.

  gh|Windows-Pics|/Program-Files-x86/Windows-Kits/n/Debuggers/_arch_/gflags.exe/kernel.png||

}
